Purpose:
nvll_osd library implements helper functions to draw rectangles/bounding boxes/segmentation mask
which are used by 'nvdsosd' plugin

Pre-requisites:
1. Install pango package:
   sudo apt-get install libpango1.0-dev

2. Install cairo package:
   sudo apt-get install libcairo2-dev

3. Install jpeg package:
   sudo apt-get install libjpeg-dev
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Compiling and installing the plugin:

export CUDA_VER=<version> or set appropriate CUDA_VER in the Makefile.
      For x86, CUDA_VER=13.1
      For Jetson & SBSA, CUDA_VER=13.0

Run:
- sudo make
- sudo make install

NOTE: To compile the sources, run make with "sudo" or root permission.
